{
  "id": "019d3163-e425-7190-b608-8fe9ed6ed5ef",
  "content": "## GC Safeguards Implementation (Issue #20)\n\nAdded 5 safety mechanisms to the GC worker to prevent harmful tier transitions:\n\n### Key Design Decisions\n\n1. **Safeguard pipeline ordering**: chain protection → auto-protection → rate limit → budget → circuit breaker. This ordering ensures chain/auto protection filters run before rate limiting (so protected entries don't consume rate limit slots), and budget runs last to handle any remaining excess.\n\n2. **Chain protection uses cycle-safe visited set**: The `build_chain_protected_set` function walks `superseded_by` pointers backward from HEADs. A `visited` HashSet prevents infinite loops on corrupted supersession cycles. Only ancestors are chain-protected; HEADs themselves are covered by auto-protection rule 2.\n\n3. **Budget resolves from global defaults, not per-type**: `budget_top_n` is scope-wide. The budget policy reads `forgetting.defaults.budget_top_n` directly with optional scope override, bypassing the per-type resolution layer. This prevents a per-type `budget_top_n` override (e.g., on Episodic) from silently changing the scope-wide cap.\n\n4. **Auto-protected entries floored at Warm under budget**: Budget can demote auto-protected Hot entries to Warm but not further. This preserves their searchability (Warm is HNSW-indexed) while still allowing budget to reclaim active slots.\n\n5. **Circuit breaker evaluates cumulative failure rate**: Uses `failed_batches / total_batches > 0.50` threshold. This is conservative — early failures are diluted by total count. A future enhancement could use consecutive-failure detection for faster response.\n\n6. **AutoProtectParams uses borrowed &str**: The `content_role` field is `Option<&'a str>` (not `Option<String>`) to avoid per-entry heap allocation in the hot scoring loop.\n\n### Files Modified\n- `crates/corvia-kernel/src/gc_worker.rs` — safeguard pipeline, chain protection, budget policy, rate limit, circuit breaker\n- `crates/corvia-kernel/src/scoring.rs` — `is_auto_protected()` with 4 rules\n\nPR: chunzhe10/corvia#44",
